text: Arundel Cathedral is a Roman Catholic church in West Sussex in Southern England. It was built in 1868. It is dedicated to Our Lady and Saint Philip Howard, the 20th Earl of Arundel, who died in the Tower of London under Queen Elizabeth I. ==Other websites== *Cathedral website Category:Cathedrals in England Category:Roman Catholic churches Category:Buildings and structures in West Sussex
title: Arundel Cathedral
